comments: when you hear about micro or macro you hear about everyone trying to get you to sign up for morshed\'s class because she is the best. in the begining she scares off students who dont care about school then she will become everyones best friend i love her to death !
I did not like her teaching style. She treated us all like a bunch of children. Did not like her
There is a lot of work for this class but it\'s all manageable. Getting an A is guaranteed as long as you do you work and read your chapters! I would highly recommend this professor.

Student success is Tahmina\xe2\x80\x99s goal. Show up, don\xe2\x80\x99t leave early, be prepared, do the homework, and study, and you can have an A. I took Macro & Micro with her and loved the classes. This is a rare adjunct instructor who actually cares for her students.
Best instructor on this campus, if you attend you will succeed. She is great!!!

Great Instructor. 4 tests+final, notes on 3 tests+final, 4 HW assignments and if you show up to class, she gives the answers. Take bonus when offered. Show up for class, take good notes and you will do well. DO NOT SKIP CLASS OR LEAVE EARLY! That ticks her off and you WILL miss something vital.

Great Instructor. 4 tests+final, notes on 3 tests+final, 4 HW assignments and if you show up to class, she gives the answers. Take bonus when offered. Show up for class, take good notes and you will do well. DO NOT SKIP CLASS OR LEAVE EARLY! That ticks her off and you WILL miss something vital.
Tahmina is an awesome professor. she grades fairly and her students are her priority. she wants to see everyone succeed
Dr. Morshed is so funny! She is super nice and helpful. She really cares about her students and their futures. She let\'s you bring a sheet of notes for a couple of the exams. She is cool!

This teacher is one of the best teachers I have ever had at Cal State San Marcos. If you show up, take good notes and participate then you will do fine. She is so funny and wants you to earn a good grade. I would definitely take her 202. 100% recommend her class!!!!!!!!!

Great teacher! 4 hw sets, to which she gives you the answers. Her tests are easy, and in some cases he will allow you to use a page of notes. NO TERM paper.If you show to class, do your hw, and take advantage of the extra credit opportunities, you will get an A. I got a B just because i missed class often. I would take her again without a doubt.

i took both 201 and 202 with her. she is very helpful and you just have to keep up with the work she assigns. her lectures are clear and just attend class everyday and take good notes. reading the book also helps if you read before and after class lectures to get what she is teaching. she also offers extra credit and its not a complicated class

Tahmina Morshed is an AWESOME professor. She is very clear in her lectures and follows a strict, easy-to-understand schedule. Tahmina will go out of her way to give you the extra help you may need. She even brings in guest speakers to give advice and establish connections in the job interview process. \r \r You won\'t regret taking her courses!
Great professor. She explained things well and did not overwhelm us with exams and assignments. Pretty easy class as long as you aren\'t a total slacker.

Great Professor she can be tough if you don\'t study. She reviews quizzes prior to giving them. 4 quizzes 4 homeworks do the homework, attend class, and pay attention to the reviews you\'ll get an A. Oh and NO cellphones she will seriously drop you from the class or fail you if its too late to drop.

There are 4 quizzes, 4 hw assignments, midterm and final She offers a 20 pt extra cr towards the end of semester. Very understanding and wants her students to really understand the course. If your not serious about class she notices and will drop you. Not mean but doesnt put up w/ interruptions Take her you\'ll be happy you did in the end!!

Very helpful and if there is a communication failure she allots time to fix the issue. 4 quizzes and homework assignments and midterm and final may allow notes on some tests but be prepared regardless. I would recommend her if you are a Econ major.

If you do not already have an understanding of economics do not take her class. She doesn\'t lay down any kind of foundation and you will be lost all semester. Not a terrible teacher to take if you do. Reading the text is necessary. Her lectures can be hard to follow and she often gets confused by students questions, not ever really answering them.

Great teacher! Dont be scared away by her tough attitude the first week of class, she does it to get rid of all the careless students. She is actually a sweet lady who can crack some funny jokes. She is tough so pay attention. She knows who is working hard and who isnt and she will repay you. Good amount of extra credit. Just take her!
Excellent
